						limited to facts contained in the officer’s personnel file concerning the disciplinary investigation or imposition of disciplinary action that specifically refute the false statements made public by the peace or custodial officer or their agent or representative.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(f) (1) The department or agency shall provide written notification to the complaining party of the disposition of the complaint within 30 days of the disposition.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) The notification described in this subdivision is not conclusive or binding or admissible as evidence in any separate or subsequent action or proceeding brought before an arbitrator, court, or judge of this state or the United States.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(g) This section does not affect the
